13:33.271 --> 13:36.104
I mean, who else is gonna
want that crazy van?
Good point.

13:36.191 --> 13:37.897
Well, like with any subculture,

13:37.985 --> 13:40.442
storm chasing attracts a variety
of distinct personality types.

13:40.570 --> 13:43.312
Adrenaline junkies.
Yeah. They’re the ones
most likely to, uh,

13:43.407 --> 13:45.443
put their lives
and the lives of others
in danger.

13:45.575 --> 13:47.611
There’s a name for them.
They’re called—
Insane.

13:47.744 --> 13:51.783
[Cell Phone Ringing]
You know, that’s a real word,
and people just throw it around.

13:51.915 --> 13:55.123
Booth.
Hemorrhagic staining on
the interior of the skull...

13:55.210 --> 13:58.452
confirms cause of death
as blunt force trauma
to the head.

13:58.547 --> 14:00.458
Good. Good news.
Any thoughts on the weapon?

14:00.549 --> 14:04.258
Based on the fracture pattern,
we’re looking for
something cylindrical,

14:04.344 --> 14:07.086
with a diameter of between
five and seven centimeters.

14:07.180 --> 14:09.967
- Right. Like a baseball bat.
- Possibly, if it were
painted orange.

14:10.100 --> 14:12.637
Any luck on the mini-mojo?
The mini-moho.

14:12.728 --> 14:14.434
Mo— That’s what I meant.

14:14.521 --> 14:17.854
Yeah, a vehicle fitting
the description’s been parked
in North Carolina for days.

14:17.941 --> 14:20.899
So, uh, you know what?
I just sent a team
to check it out.

14:20.986 --> 14:23.068
What? Wait, why—
why aren’t we going?

14:23.155 --> 14:25.237
I-If there are other
storm chasers there,

14:25.323 --> 14:27.484
we’re missing the opportunity
to exploit their expertise...

14:27.576 --> 14:30.443
and learn about the nuances
of tornado behavior

14:30.537 --> 14:32.243
Eh, it’s a four-hour drive
there and back.

14:32.330 --> 14:34.161
I didn’t think it was
good use of our time.

14:34.249 --> 14:37.662
Well— [ Sighs]
I wish you’d consulted me first.

14:37.753 --> 14:40.415
- Where are you? You sound
like you’re in the car.
