14:48.055 --> 14:50.421
I’ll let you know as soon
as I hear anything, okay?
Okay, but—

14:50.515 --> 14:52.221
[Line Beeps]

14:52.309 --> 14:54.300
Why did you tell
Dr. Brennan that—

14:54.394 --> 14:56.601
Look, do | ask you questions
about Daisy? No.

14:56.688 --> 14:59.270
No. But if there’s something
you wanna know,
I’d be happy to—

14:59.357 --> 15:02.394
There’s nothing I want to know,
and there’s nothing
I want to tell.

15:02.527 --> 15:04.358
Okay?
Well—

15:11.870 --> 15:14.282
License plate matches.
Oh, that’s a relief,

15:14.372 --> 15:17.580
’cause I really thought
there’d be more than one
armored motor home...

15:17.667 --> 15:19.874
with a satellite dish
on the roof
in the parking lot.

15:19.961 --> 15:22.498
Don’t get snippy with me
just ’cause you feel bad
about lying.

15:22.589 --> 15:25.331
[ Motor Home Creaking ]

15:25.425 --> 15:27.962
[ Sweets ]
Hey, looks like
someone’s inside.

15:28.053 --> 15:30.419
It sounds like there’s
two “someones” inside.

15:30.514 --> 15:33.551
[Woman ]
The storm.
It’s so big!

15:33.683 --> 15:37.096
So powerful!
[ Man] It’s coming right at us!
Hang on!

15:37.187 --> 15:38.768
- Seriously?
- [ Man] Here it comes!

15:38.855 --> 15:42.188
Human sexuality is a gem
with innumerable facets.

15:42.275 --> 15:45.187
[Woman Moaning]

15:46.530 --> 15:47.986
[Booth]
F.B.|. Open up.

15:48.073 --> 15:51.031
Come out with your hands up,
in the air and your pants on.

15:51.159 --> 15:53.650
[Woman]
F.B.|.?
[ Man ] Where’s my shirt?

15:53.745 --> 15:55.736
Seriously, you didn’t know
how that was gonna end?

16:00.210 --> 16:01.700
All right, thank you.

16:01.795 --> 16:03.331
Well, the girl swears
they just met.

16:03.421 --> 16:05.457
We’ll run a check.
In the meantime,
I want you to meet Nolan.

16:05.549 --> 16:08.757
He says that he’s been
Scott’s, uh, driver
for the past three seasons.

16:08.885 --> 16:11.627
[ Sweets ] Why do you
still have his vehicle?
I’ve been holding it hostage.

16:11.721 --> 16:14.884
Scott had cash flow
problems this season.
He hadn’t paid me yet.

16:14.975 --> 16:17.933
I got fed up.
Said I wasn’t gonna drive
anymore until I got paid.

16:18.019 --> 16:20.146
So what were you
doin’ out here
where all these storms hit?

16:20.230 --> 16:22.312
Were you trying
to sell this vehicle?

16:22.399 --> 16:23.935
You saw what I’m doin’.

16:24.025 --> 16:26.687
That girl—
she’s what we call
a,uh,chaserchaseh

16:26.778 --> 16:30.316
- Storm groupie.
- Someone who’s aroused
by extreme weather patterns.

16:30.407 --> 16:36.323
- It’s, uh, human sexuality—
- “Groupie” pretty much
spelled that out for me.

16:36.413 --> 16:38.745
This little baby sure has
got me a lot of tail.

16:39.958 --> 16:41.949
I’ll be sorry
to see her go.

16:42.043 --> 16:43.749
It’s a sexy vehicle.

16:54.598 --> 16:56.304
Honey.
Hmm?

16:56.391 --> 16:57.346
[Chuckles]

16:57.434 --> 17:00.392
Those are particulates,
not Michael.

17:00.478 --> 17:02.605
You don’t have to keep
moving like that.

17:02.689 --> 17:04.771
Uh, I didn’t even know
I was doing it.

17:04.858 --> 17:09.318
[ Sighs ]
Michael only falls asleep
when l oscillate.

17:09.446 --> 17:12.108
Coffee wore off, huh?
Yeah.

17:12.199 --> 17:14.030
We’ll get through this.

17:14.159 --> 17:15.820
So these are
the particulates?
Yeah.

17:15.911 --> 17:18.948
If you cross-reference
the concentration
of various particulates...

17:19.039 --> 17:21.997
with the topographical data
you have regarding
the storm’s path,

17:22.083 --> 17:23.584
then you can determine
the murder site.

17:23.710 --> 17:27.919
Oh, honey.
You’re so brilliant.
You too.

17:28.006 --> 17:32.215
- Whoa. Tryin’ to make
another kid?
- Hi, Dad.

17:32.302 --> 17:36.796
Stopped into day care, and it
turns out they don’t seem to
have those rules you made up.

17:37.807 --> 17:40.594
Oh, uh, I can explain that.
That’s—

17:40.685 --> 17:44.519
I’m getting the feelin’ that
you don’t trust me to be alone
with my own grandbaby.

17:44.606 --> 17:46.642
Of course we do.

17:46.733 --> 17:49.566
[ Chuckles ]
That’s so not true.

17:49.653 --> 17:52.895
I played stadiums every night
back when you were in diapers.

17:52.989 --> 17:55.480
And you were backstage
at every single show.

17:55.575 --> 17:57.281
You think that did her
any harm?

17:57.369 --> 18:01.078
All the books say that
a strict routine is crucial.

18:01.164 --> 18:04.281
So, we just wanna be there
when you’re with him...

18:04.376 --> 18:06.708
until he gets regulated.

18:06.795 --> 18:08.751
Well, I’m leavin’ tomorrow,
baby girl.

18:08.838 --> 18:11.250
And, uh, it doesn’t seem right
for that little guy...

18:11.341 --> 18:15.334
to miss out on even
one minute of hangin’
with his grandpa.

18:20.642 --> 18:25.636
So, the National Science
Federation’s making a, uh,
IMAX film about tornadoes.

18:25.730 --> 18:27.721
Let me guess.
Scott was trying
to get the contract?

18:27.816 --> 18:31.058
Right. So the filmmaker
is gonna ride along
with the storm chaser...

18:31.152 --> 18:33.529
for five seasons,
gathering footage.

18:33.613 --> 18:35.820
- How much is
the contract worth?
- Half a million dollars.

18:35.907 --> 18:37.613
[ Blows ]

18:37.701 --> 18:40.363
That was supposed
to be a whistle.
My tongue’s coated with cheese.

18:40.453 --> 18:42.865
Look at the, uh, storm chaser
who got the contract.

18:42.956 --> 18:44.912
Antonia “Toni” Lawrence.

18:45.000 --> 18:47.082
[ Blows ]

18:47.210 --> 18:48.711
Yeah, I need some water.
Right.

18:48.795 --> 18:54.006
Turns out that Scott
had Toni arrested last year.

18:54.092 --> 18:55.798
Criminal mischief?

18:55.885 --> 18:59.173
He accused her of putting sugar
in his gas tank to keep him
away from the storms.

18:59.264 --> 19:01.880
I mean, the charges were
eventually dropped.

19:02.017 --> 19:03.803
But still, right?
Right.

19:03.893 --> 19:06.976
Well, Toni must be
around here somewhere, right,
considering the storm system.

19:07.063 --> 19:09.270
The Bureau is tracing
her credit cards now.

19:13.069 --> 19:14.775
Why are you lying
to Dr. Brennan?

19:14.863 --> 19:18.355
I mean, you told her
that a team was going
to North Carolina.

19:18.491 --> 19:20.322
That’s us.
There’s a lot
of storms out here.

19:20.410 --> 19:22.150
I don’t want her
in this environment.

19:22.245 --> 19:23.746
I’m just trying
to be protective.

19:23.830 --> 19:26.537
Of course she’s gonna think
that I’m, you know,
overly protective.

19:26.624 --> 19:29.457
- Aren’t you though?
- Ah.

19:29.544 --> 19:32.877
Okay, look, I’m just saying,
Dr. Brennan is an adult.

19:32.964 --> 19:35.080
- She’s your partner, both
personally and professionally.
- [Cell Phone Ringing]

19:35.216 --> 19:39.084
And while it’s understandable—
Okay, we got the location
for Toni Lawrence.

19:39.179 --> 19:40.168
Okay.

19:40.263 --> 19:41.844
[Whistles ]
There we go.

19:41.931 --> 19:43.512
[ Whistles ]

19:43.600 --> 19:45.511
[ Fisher]
No, Mom, I can’t.

19:45.602 --> 19:48.810
I’m not gonna marry her, Mom.
I can’t even remember
her name.

19:49.773 --> 19:51.855
Emma? Huh.

19:51.941 --> 19:54.023
Could’ve sworn
it’s sort of a “juh” sound.

19:54.110 --> 19:56.317
[ Chuckling ]
Wow!
Gotta go. Bye.

19:56.404 --> 19:58.816
This is tremendous!

19:58.907 --> 20:01.865
The FBI. already
examined it for evidence.
They couldn’t find anything.

20:01.951 --> 20:05.443
Dr. Saroyan said they could
store it here until a spot
opens up at their garage.

20:05.580 --> 20:08.447
Hey, can we go inside?
Uh, we probably shouldn’t.

20:17.592 --> 20:20.083
[ Metal Squeaking ]

20:27.477 --> 20:30.093
Okay, let’s deploy
the first two sensors.

20:30.188 --> 20:32.930
We’re gonna leave
those here, all right?
Everything else, we gotta—

20:33.024 --> 20:35.766
[ Booth ]
Sweets, look at all the camera
equipment over here, huh?

20:35.860 --> 20:38.067
Hey, you the ones that are
shooting the movie?

20:38.154 --> 20:42.898
- Yeah, is there a problem?
- Wait, I’m Misty Clemmons,
one of the project coordinators.

20:42.992 --> 20:44.778
Sorry, no tourists
on this run.

20:44.869 --> 20:47.531
- You’re Toni Lawrence, right?
- A fan. Nice to meet you.

20:47.622 --> 20:50.455
F.B.|. Special Agent Booth.
This here is Dr. Sweets.

20:50.542 --> 20:53.329
Yeah. We’re here to ask you
about your rivalry
with Scott Braley.

20:53.420 --> 20:54.830
Rivalry?

20:54.921 --> 20:57.583
I’ve got a four-vehicle crew,
a thriving tour service.

20:57.674 --> 21:00.290
I’m a regular commentator
on The Weather Channel.

21:00.385 --> 21:02.751
Scott’s a lone storm weirdo.
There’s no rivalry.

21:02.846 --> 21:05.804
Really?
You damaged his gas tank.
Sounds like a rivalry to me.

21:05.890 --> 21:08.506
If you’ll excuse me.
There’s a mesocyclone
developing.

21:08.601 --> 21:11.764
Meso— Oh!

21:11.855 --> 21:13.846
[ Toni ]
I’ve gotta get my crew
on the road.

21:13.940 --> 21:16.477
You gonna cut me some slack
for lying to Bones now?

21:16.568 --> 21:18.308
Yeah. No, you should—
totally should’ve lied.

21:20.029 --> 21:23.021
Whoa, whoa, whoa! Wait a second.
Look at the extinguisher
on her truck.

21:23.116 --> 21:24.481
[Toni]
Hurry up!
Let’s go, guys.

21:24.576 --> 21:26.237
Bones was telling me
about a potential
murder weapon.

21:26.327 --> 21:28.943
It’s the same
shape and color.
I gotta get this.

21:29.080 --> 21:31.787
[ Crashing ]
Agent Booth!

21:31.875 --> 21:34.833
Stop Toni and the crew
from leaving.
You understand?

21:35.962 --> 21:38.419
It’s all right, honey.
I’m more worried about you.

21:38.548 --> 21:42.336
Come on! Everyone into
the shelter for questioning.
No.

21:42.427 --> 21:45.544
- We have to get on the road—
- [ Crashing ]

21:48.683 --> 21:50.969
Come on!
Come on down here!

21:51.060 --> 21:55.474
[All Shouting]

21:55.565 --> 21:57.772
Don’t worry about it!
Go! Go! Go!

21:59.944 --> 22:02.356
Hey, Booth. Come on!
Go, go, go!

22:03.698 --> 22:05.279
[ Man Shouting]

22:05.366 --> 22:07.448
[ Man #2 ]
Get that guy
in here!

22:14.292 --> 22:16.533
Booth, get in here!

22:16.628 --> 22:18.118
[ Man ]
Close the hatch!

22:24.344 --> 22:26.300
This is a big one.
This is huge.

22:26.387 --> 22:29.379
I didn’t think
we were gonna make it.

22:31.142 --> 22:33.519
- You lied to me!
- Bones, what are you doing?

22:33.603 --> 22:36.015
Get inside!
Come on. Easy.

22:36.105 --> 22:37.641
I couldn’t miss this.

22:40.944 --> 22:43.651
You know, you could’ve
killed yourself, Bones.
But I didn’t. I’m fine.

22:43.738 --> 22:45.353
How’d you even know
where to find us?

22:45.448 --> 22:46.949
I used the cell tower
ping method...

22:47.033 --> 22:50.116
that led us to
Vincent Nigel-Murray’s killer.

22:50.203 --> 22:52.410
This could definitely be
the murder weapon.

22:52.497 --> 22:53.987
I’m telling you,
I didn’t kill him.

22:54.082 --> 22:55.538
I didn’t even know
Scott was missing.

22:55.625 --> 22:58.742
Right, but you knew
that he wanted that
film contract, right?

22:58.836 --> 23:01.327
- [ Clattering Outside]
- [Toni] I cannot believe
you made us miss this.

23:01.422 --> 23:03.208
How about you? How long
