23:03.299 --> 23:05.210
Wait, wait, wait.
Don’t suck me into this.

23:05.301 --> 23:06.882
Look, l-l just shoot
the storms.

23:06.970 --> 23:09.211
Toni led me to the best footage,
and that’s as far as we go.

23:09.305 --> 23:13.264
I’ve been doing some reading
on the rotational behavior
of tornadoes.

23:13.351 --> 23:15.216
- Have either of you—
- Is this really relevant?

23:15.311 --> 23:17.222
This is my first
tornado case, Booth.
Find out—

23:17.313 --> 23:19.053
You know, you could’ve
just used the telephone.

23:19.148 --> 23:22.060
Well, I find it easier
to have direct conversation.

23:22.151 --> 23:23.982
Right. ’Cause it’s
always important
to have face time...

23:24.070 --> 23:26.482
right before
you’re about to get blown
into the side of a barn.

23:26.573 --> 23:28.734
- [ Clattering Outside]
- Whoa!

23:28.825 --> 23:30.690
[ Man ]
Man, this one’s huge.

23:30.785 --> 23:33.242
Okay, did you ever shoot film
with Scott Braley too?

23:33.329 --> 23:36.446
I tried. I met with him
in Virginia last month
during the storms there,

23:36.541 --> 23:39.533
and he said he’d call me
next time he went out,
but he never did though.

23:39.627 --> 23:42.960
Okay. Well, when that, uh,
huge tornado hit,
where were you?

23:43.047 --> 23:46.255
l was sitting in
my motel room like an idiot,
waiting for him to call.

23:46.342 --> 23:48.253
- I missed
the whole entire thing.
- [Objects Crashing Outside]

23:48.344 --> 23:50.756
And now,
I’m missing another one.

23:50.847 --> 23:53.759
Did you hear that?
Mother Nature is so incredible.

23:53.850 --> 23:55.431
Mother Nature is not real.

23:55.518 --> 23:57.804
Okay, how about you?
You have any dealings
with Scott?

23:57.895 --> 24:00.728
Oh, I don’t get to spend much
time with the actual chasers.

24:00.815 --> 24:02.680
I mostly just drive the film
back and forth.

24:02.775 --> 24:05.642
Mm-hmm. And I see you’re also
a big fan of, uh, rainbows.

24:05.737 --> 24:08.194
I love them.
God’s promise after every storm.

24:08.281 --> 24:10.988
[Objects Crashing ]

24:14.704 --> 24:16.490
- What do you mean? Who?
- I don’t know.

24:16.581 --> 24:20.119
I heard him on the phone
about a month and a half ago.
We were at the same rest stop.

24:20.209 --> 24:21.745
He was screaming at someone.
It was ugly.

24:21.836 --> 24:24.703
- Okay.
What were they arguing about?
- Sounded like money.

24:24.797 --> 24:28.540
From what I could tell,
whoever Scott was yelling at,
Scott owed a lot.

24:29.969 --> 24:33.052
[Objects Crashing ]

24:36.893 --> 24:40.135
,r Don ’t forget ,r,r
